Description: Intact pottery jar with a cylindrical neck, almost straight vertical sides and a rounded base. Probably red slipped.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Naukratis, Well A (= Hogarth site 36)
Curator's comments: Excavated from a well by Hogarth in 1899 and said to be given to Bulak Museum in Cairo, although this object was not found registered in Cairo, Egyptian Museum (Edgar 1905, 123-5, Fig.3). The collection of pottery from this well was dated by von Bissing to 525-323BC (Edgar 1905, 124-5) but this dating is too late for this jar, which is typically Saite.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IB.049)
Exhibition history: Thought to be stored in Cairo, Egyptian Museum
